div.P:
A PLATFORM-AGNOSTIC COMMAND-LINE TOOL FOR ENCRYPTING AND DECRYPTING CONFIGURATION FILES, SUCH AS YAML, JSON, AND INI FILES.
IT PROVIDES A SIMPLE AND SECURE WAY TO STORE SENSITIVE INFORMATION, LIKE PASSWORDS, API KEYS, AND OTHER SECRETS, IN PLAIN TEXT FILES.

ul.li: SOPS AUTOMATICALLY HANDLES KEY ROTATION AND FALLBACK MECHANISMS, ENSURING SEAMLESS ENCRYPTION AND DECRYPTION.
THE ENCRYPTION METHOD INFORMATION IS STORED AS PART OF THE FILE, ALLOWING SOPS TO DETERMINE THE CORRECT DECRYPTION METHOD WITHOUT USER INTERVENTION.

text.tspan: OR DECRYPTION OPERATION ON A FILE.
INCLUDING ENCRYPTION METHOD AND KEY INFORMATION

g.text: SOPS USES THE SELECTED KEY TO ENCRYPT OR DECRYPT THE FILE.
USER READS OR WRITES TO FILE.

text.tspan: IF THE FILE IS MODIFIED DURING DECRYPTION,
USING THE ORIGINAL ENCRYPTION METHOD AND KEY.

g.text: THE ENCRYPTED OR DECRYPTED FILE IS SAVED TO ITS ORIGINAL LOCATION.
